Geez is an independent quarterly Canadian magazine dealing with issues of spirituality, social justice, religion, and progressive cultural politics. The tagline of Geez is "holy mischief in an age of fast faith". Geez is based in Winnipeg, Manitoba and distributes in Canada, the U.S and abroad. Founded by Aiden Enns (Buy Nothing Christmas) and Will Braun, Geez looks at religion, spirituality, and politics through the eyes of its readers. Geez is known for its pointed illustrations, clever graphics and unique combination of satire, critique, social consciousness, and quirkiness.
